-- Capital Estate to Sell Up to HK$135 Million of Convertible Notes Due 2013
-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 2010-10-14T13:47:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-14/capital-estate-to-sell-up-to-hk-135-million-of-convertible-notes-due-2013.html
Capital Estate Ltd . will issue as
much as HK$135 million of 4 percent notes due in 2013 and
convertible into new shares at 36 Hong Kong cents each, the
company said in a Hong Kong stock exchange filing today.  Get Nice Securities Ltd. will acting as placing agent for
the best-effort sale, receiving a commission of 2.5 percent of
the aggregate principal, Capital Estate said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  